awing on extensive work in urban history and Progressive politics, Benjamin Heber Johnson weaves together environmental history, material culture, and politics to reveal the successes and failures of the conservation movement and its lasting legacy. By following the efforts of a broad range of people and groups—women’s clubs, labor advocates, architects, and politicians—Johnson shows how conservation embodied the ideals of Progressivism, ultimately becoming one of its most important legacies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aConservation of natural resourcesxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironmentalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aNature conservationxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aProgressivism (United States politics)xHistoryy20th century. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060420708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018z9783110603200oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106389810 cprintz978030011550540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300227765423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300227765/original  a978-3-11-060420-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  